Generate me the gitignore so it doesnt upload the node_modules

Your TXT file is ready
TXT icon
gitignore
 TXT 
Open

I have generated a comprehensive ignore file for your Node.js project. It includes the node_modules/ folder as requested, as well as standard exclusions for things like environment variables (.env), debug logs, and OS-specific hidden files (like .DS_Store or Thumbs.db).

To use this file:

Download the file above.

Place it in the root folder of your project (where your package.json is located).

Rename the file from gitignore.txt to exactly .gitignore (make sure it starts with a dot).

This will immediately prevent Git from tracking and uploading your node_modules folder.






